You are reviewing a pull request for an EmptyState component in a Raycast UI clone project. The project uses React 19, TypeScript strict mode, Sass (BEM naming), and Bun.

Review the following files as a senior engineer doing a thorough PR review. Check for:
1. Correctness and completeness against the spec
2. Consistency with existing component patterns in the project
3. CSS/Sass issues (missing tokens, hardcoded values, wrong patterns)
4. TypeScript issues
5. Accessibility concerns
6. Any workarounds or shortcuts

**Spec (from progress.txt):**
EmptyState component (src/components/empty_state/). Centered message shown when list has no results. Icon (large, 48x48), title ($font-lg, $text-primary), and optional description ($font-sm, $text-secondary). Flex column, align-items center, justify-content center. Padding $space-8. Takes full available height.

**New file: src/components/empty_state/empty_state.tsx**
```tsx
import type { ReactNode } from 'react';
import './empty_state.scss';

export interface EmptyStateProps {
  icon: ReactNode;
  title: string;
  description?: string;
}

export function EmptyState({ icon, title, description }: EmptyStateProps) {
  return (
    <div className="empty-state">
      <div className="empty-state__icon">{icon}</div>
      <h2 className="empty-state__title">{title}</h2>
      {description && <p className="empty-state__description">{description}</p>}
    </div>
  );
}
```

**New file: src/components/empty_state/empty_state.scss**
```scss
